post_text: Notice-The Woodson School District has identified multiple students who had close contact with a presumptive positive COVID student. In conjunction with Woodson County Health, these students are being asked to quarantine for 14-days. All but one of the contacts are at the 9-12 level, with the other at the middle school level. It is very important that all students be routinely observed for COVID symptoms before attending school. These symptoms include fever or chills, cough, sore throat, shortness of breath or difficulty breathing, fatigue, muscle or body aches, headache, new loss of taste or smell, Congestion or runny nose, nausea or vomiting, or diarrhea. If any student is experiencing any of these symptoms, please keep students at home. Should additional information need to be shared regarding this notice, the district will get it to you as soon as possible.

The USDA granting Free meals to all is a great benefit for all families who didn't qualify for free meals. However, parents we still need you to fill out the Free and Reduced lunch applications.

1) This program can be ended at any time and parents will be responsible for meals eaten until the form is completed
2) Kansas awards at-risk funding to schools based on those forms. No forms = no at-risk funding the programs our kids depend upon.

Please visit our website to get the application or call the school/district office and we can send it out to you.

Elementary/MS Building Visitors
‚Ä¢ The building is not accepting visitors. If you need to come to the building for school business, please call the office for a time to come to the office. If you need to pick up your student, please call the school office, and we will attempt to have them ready for you. During the school day circle drive pickup is acceptable. There is one exception to the no visiting rule, and this deals with kindergarten and first-grade students. The first seven days, the end of the first full week, parents may walk their students to the classrooms. The wearing of masks of those walking students to class or entering the building would be much appreciated.

post_text: Elementary/MS Breakfast/Lunch - Through student arrival communication, breakfast has been addressed. Breakfast will be a grab and go meal, which is taken to the classroom of the student. Grade levels have been paired by using K-1, 2-3, 4-5, and 6-8. Grade levels will alternate on a two-week cycle of eating in the gym or the classroom unless an agreement to change is made by the grade-level groups. In middle school, the smallest class, 7th grade, will dine in Mr. McVey‚Äôs classroom under Mr. McVey‚Äôs guidance.

post_text:
By now, I‚Äôm assuming everyone is aware that we will have a delayed start to school. It appears that school will not begin until September 8th. This change will require the district to change the calendar to address the requirements of the state in meeting the number of hours students will have to attend school.

Hopefully, with this delay, we will be better prepared to open the buildings back up. We should learn more later today when we have our state Zoom meeting with the state department. A group of teachers and myself will be listing in on this meeting in hopes of understanding what we have to do and what is going to be required. Once we know the parameters of opening the buildings, we will begin working on a district plan to reopen. As more information is available, we will attempt to keep you informed as to what is taking place.

post_text: If your household‚Äôs eligibility for free or reduced price meals for SY2019-2020, your student(s) are eligible for a Pandemic EBT benefit to equal the value of the meals the child(ren) would have received at school. If your household already receives Food Assistance, TANF, Child Care or Medicaid benefits no further action is needed. This benefit will automatically be added to your Kansas Benefits Card (or you will be mailed a Kansas Benefits Card if only on Medicaid). Kansas will continue to comply with civil rights requirements, to include providing equal access to individuals with disabilities and individuals who are limited English proficient.
